@learn-loop/core
================

The rule-engine pattern and declarative rule schema in this package
(src/engine/applyAction.ts, src/model/scenario.ts) are adapted to TypeScript from
the MIT-licensed project:

    chem_lab — https://github.com/nsriram/chem_lab
    Copyright (c) nsriram, MIT License

Only the engine pattern (a first-match-wins rule registry resolving an action
against a station's contents into a result) and the rule-schema shape were ported.
This package generalises and de-chemistry's that core into a domain-agnostic
"guided-sim" engine — a workspace of named stations holding entities, an
action/transform vocabulary (react / split / evaporate / distil), the per-step
Predict → Observe → Explain session loop, tap-gating, and stage geometry. That
generalisation, the neutral model (Scenario / Entity / Rule / StepResult), and the
React UI shells are original to this project.

Design lineage: this package was authored fresh, informed by the shipped
chemistry-lab-bench game in this repository (which carries its own NOTICE). No code
was extracted by modifying that game; it was left untouched as a reference.
